    "text": "You're right that duration isn't the story: last night was 405 minutes, about 6.8 h, exactly your weekly average of 6.8 h. Two things stand out instead. First, consistent doesn't mean sufficient; 6.8 h may simply be under what you need, and the tiredness is the tell. Second, your resting heart rate is 64 bpm this morning against a 30-day average of 60.5, a noticeable bump even though HRV is normal at 49 ms, which can accompany accumulated load like yesterday's hard 31-minute hike at a 15.2 load. The experiment I'd run: push bedtime fifteen minutes earlier for a week and see whether the morning tiredness and that resting heart rate both come down. I can't see sleep stages in your data, so depth is a blind spot here.",
